creditline: Gift of Elizabeth, Julie, and Catherine Andrus in memory of John and Marion Andrus
description: man at center with his PR hand up and a lighter coloring around his head; a group of men gathered around him in an interior space; matted and in frame with four other prints

provenance: John H. Wrenn (1841-1911), Lugt 1475, Chicago. John E. Andrus III, Wayzata, Minn.; by descent to his daughters, Elizabeth, Katie, and Julie; gave to MIA, 2015. Earlier provenances have been gathered, but further research will increase our knowledge of their histories.
title: The Tribute Money
